---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Enterprise — SessionFS" activeNav="enterprise" description="Self-hosted SessionFS on Kubernetes. Your data stays on your infrastructure.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-32 sm:pt-40 pb-16 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="fade-up font-heading text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
        Deploy anywhere.<br>Control everything.
      </h1>
      <p class="fade-up text-lg sm:text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto mb-4">
        Self-hosted Kubernetes deployment with Helm. Your data stays on your infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p class="fade-up text-base text-muted-dim max-w-lg mx-auto">Enterprise-tested on AWS EKS. Works on GKE, AKS, and on-prem clusters.</p>
      <div class="fade-up mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center">
        <a href="mailto:enterprise@sessionfs.dev?subject=SessionFS%20Enterprise" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-brand text-white font-semibold rounded-lg px-7 py-3 hover:brightness-110 transition">
          Contact Enterprise Sales
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/quickstart/" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 border border-border text-txt font-semibold rounded-lg px-7 py-3 hover:border-muted transition">
          View docs
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- Helm terminal + deployment highlight -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-12">
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-5">One Helm chart. Any cluster.</h2>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">Deploy to AWS EKS, GCP GKE, Azure AKS, or on-prem Kubernetes with a single command. The Helm chart handles API, dashboard, daemon config, ingress, PostgreSQL, and license validation.</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">Bring your own object store — S3, GCS, or local PVC. Connect to an existing PostgreSQL (RDS, Cloud SQL, or the bundled instance).</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm bg-surface border border-border rounded px-3 py-1.5 text-muted-dim">AWS EKS</span>
          <span class="font-mono text-sm bg-surface border border-border rounded px-3 py-1.5 text-muted-dim">GCP GKE</span>
          <span class="font-mono text-sm bg-surface border border-border rounded px-3 py-1.5 text-muted-dim">Azure AKS</span>
          <span class="font-mono text-sm bg-surface border border-border rounded px-3 py-1.5 text-muted-dim">On-prem</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 w-full fade-up">
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="hero-glow"></div>
          <div class="term relative z-10">
            <div class="term-bar">
              <div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
              <div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
              <div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
              <span class="ml-3 text-muted-dim text-[13px] font-mono">helm deploy</span>
            </div>
            <div class="p-5 font-mono text-sm space-y-3">
              <div>
                <span class="text-muted-dim">$</span>
                <span class="text-accent"> helm install sessionfs ./charts/sessionfs \</span>
              </div>
              <div class="pl-4 text-accent">--set api.image=ghcr.io/sessionfs/api:v0.9.5 \</div>
              <div class="pl-4 text-accent">--set storage.backend=s3 \</div>
              <div class="pl-4 text-accent">--set storage.bucket=my-sessions-bucket \</div>
              <div class="pl-4 text-accent">--values values.prod.yaml</div>
              <div class="border-t border-border pt-3 text-muted">
                Release "sessionfs" has been deployed.<br>
                <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> API ready at api.internal.company.com<br>
                <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Dashboard ready at sessions.company.com<br>
                <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> PostgreSQL migrations applied (10 migrations)
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- Feature cards -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 bg-surface/50 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="fade-up font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Built for engineering teams</h2>
      <p class="fade-up text-muted text-center mb-14 max-w-lg mx-auto leading-relaxed">Everything you need to run SessionFS at scale, on your own infrastructure.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">

        <div class="glass fade-up p-6">
          <div class="mb-3"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#4f9cf7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M16.5 10.5V6.75a4.5 4.5 0 10-9 0v3.75m-.75 11.25h10.5a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-6.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25-2.25H6.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25 2.25v6.75a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Data sovereignty</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mb-4 leading-relaxed">Your bucket, your database, your infrastructure. Session data never leaves your network. No callbacks, no telemetry, no surprise egress.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-dim text-sm">S3, GCS, or local PVC &middot; PostgreSQL (RDS, Cloud SQL, or built-in)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass fade-up p-6">
          <div class="mb-3"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#4f9cf7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">AI governance</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mb-4 leading-relaxed">Complete audit trail of every AI agent action across your team. LLM Judge with severity-classified findings, stored audit history, and model comparison over time.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-dim text-sm">Auto-audit on sync or PR/MR &middot; Contradiction reports in PR comments</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass fade-up p-6">
          <div class="mb-3"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#4f9cf7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.594 3.94c.09-.542.56-.94 1.11-.94h2.593c.55 0 1.02.398 1.11.94l.213 1.281c.063.374.313.686.645.87.074.04.147.083.22.127.324.196.72.257 1.075.124l1.217-.456a1.125 1.125 0 011.37.49l1.296 2.247a1.125 1.125 0 01-.26 1.431l-1.003.827c-.293.24-.438.613-.431.992a6.759 6.759 0 010 .255c-.007.378.138.75.43.99l1.005.828c.424.35.534.954.26 1.43l-1.298 2.247a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.369.491l-1.217-.456c-.355-.133-.75-.072-1.076.124a6.57 6.57 0 01-.22.128c-.331.183-.581.495-.644.869l-.213 1.28c-.09.543-.56.941-1.11.941h-2.594c-.55 0-1.02-.398-1.11-.94l-.213-1.281c-.062-.374-.312-.686-.644-.87a6.52 6.52 0 01-.22-.127c-.325-.196-.72-.257-1.076-.124l-1.217.456a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.369-.49l-1.297-2.247a1.125 1.125 0 01.26-1.431l1.004-.827c.292-.24.437-.613.43-.992a6.932 6.932 0 010-.255c.007-.378-.138-.75-.43-.99l-1.004-.828a1.125 1.125 0 01-.26-1.43l1.297-2.247a1.125 1.125 0 011.37-.491l1.216.456c.356.133.751.072 1.076-.124.072-.044.146-.087.22-.128.332-.183.582-.495.644-.869l.214-1.281z"/><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Your LLM gateway</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mb-4 leading-relaxed">Bring your own LLM — connect the Judge to your internal gateway and never expose API keys to developers. Works with any OpenAI-compatible endpoint.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-dim text-sm">LiteLLM, vLLM, Ollama, Azure OpenAI, Anthropic, Google</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass fade-up p-6">
          <div class="mb-3"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#4f9cf7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 19.128a9.38 9.38 0 002.625.372 9.337 9.337 0 004.121-.952 4.125 4.125 0 00-7.533-2.493M15 19.128v-.003c0-1.113-.285-2.16-.786-3.07M15 19.128v.106A12.318 12.318 0 018.624 21c-2.331 0-4.512-.645-6.374-1.766l-.001-.109a6.375 6.375 0 0111.964-3.07M12 6.375a3.375 3.375 0 11-6.75 0 3.375 3.375 0 016.75 0zm8.25 2.25a2.625 2.625 0 11-5.25 0 2.625 2.625 0 015.25 0z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Team handoff at scale</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mb-4 leading-relaxed">Engineers hand off sessions with full context — conversation, workspace state, git snapshot. Paths auto-resolve by git remote URL across different machines.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-dim text-sm">Email notifications via Resend, SMTP, or air-gapped (no email)</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- Security & Compliance -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-start gap-12">
        <div class="lg:w-1/2 fade-up">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-5">Security &amp; compliance</h2>
          <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">Designed for regulated industries and security-conscious teams. SessionFS self-hosted gives you complete control over access, storage, and audit trails.</p>
          <a href="mailto:enterprise@sessionfs.dev?subject=SessionFS%20Compliance" class="text-brand hover:underline text-sm font-medium">Ask about compliance requirements &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-1/2 fade-up">
          <div class="glass p-6 space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent text-lg mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">HIPAA-ready deployment</div>
                <div class="text-muted text-base">Air-gapped install with no external network calls. All session data stays within your VPC.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border pt-4 flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent text-lg mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SAML SSO</div>
                <div class="text-muted text-base">Integrate with Okta, Azure AD, or any SAML 2.0 identity provider for centralized access control.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border pt-4 flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent text-lg mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Full audit log</div>
                <div class="text-muted text-base">Every session write, push, handoff, and audit is logged with user, timestamp, and IP. Exportable for SIEM.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border pt-4 flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent text-lg mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Organizations + RBAC</div>
                <div class="text-muted text-base">Admin and member roles with organization management. Team-scoped session visibility with per-repo isolation and tier-based feature gating.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border pt-4 flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent text-lg mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SLA &amp; dedicated support</div>
                <div class="text-muted text-base">Guaranteed uptime SLA, named support contact, and direct Slack channel for enterprise accounts.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative py-16 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <div class="glass fade-up p-8 sm:p-10 text-center" style="border-color: rgba(79,156,247,0.3);">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-3">Talk to the team</h2>
        <p class="text-muted mb-2 leading-relaxed">Self-hosted deployment, compliance requirements, custom SLA, and pricing for large teams.</p>
        <p class="text-muted-dim text-sm mb-8">We typically respond within one business day.</p>
        <a href="mailto:enterprise@sessionfs.dev?subject=SessionFS%20Enterprise" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-brand text-white font-semibold rounded-lg px-8 py-3.5 hover:brightness-110 transition">
          Contact Enterprise Sales
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); } });
  }, { threshold: 0.1 });
  document.querySelectorAll('.fade-up').forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>
